History: History: F with fatigue and weakness, r/o pnuemonia.
Findings: The heart remains enlarged. The aorta is markedly tortuous. Increased interstitial markings are seen throughout the lungs, similar to prior, and most compatible with edema. No pneumothorax or consolidation or pleural effusion. There is diffuse demineralization. Incidental note is made of a right cervical rib. Sternotomy sutures project over the mediastinum. EKG leads overlie the chest wall.
